the person is just a holder,

00:07:42.255 --> 00:07:45.435
not an HDC for check specifics.

00:07:45.555 --> 00:07:51.045
Always, always remember a check is drawn
on a bank and is payable on demand.

00:07:51.495 --> 00:07:54.080
This is what separates it
from other bills of exchange.

00:07:54.930 --> 00:07:57.570
Finally understand the liability flow.

00:07:57.990 --> 00:08:02.910
Generally, the primary liability is
on the maker of a promissory note or

00:08:02.940 --> 00:08:05.100
the acceptor of a bill of exchange.

00:08:05.520 --> 00:08:09.780
The secondary liability falls
on the drawer and any endorsers,

00:08:10.650 --> 00:08:12.930
common mistakes and misconceptions.

00:08:13.425 --> 00:08:15.465
Let's talk about the common traps.

00:08:15.825 --> 00:08:19.485
Many people confuse a promissory
note and a bill of exchange.

00:08:19.905 --> 00:08:22.515
Just remember, a note is a promise.

00:08:22.635 --> 00:08:24.015
A bill is an order.

00:08:24.195 --> 00:08:25.575
That's the core difference.

00:08:25.965 --> 00:08:27.765
Another mistake is thinking.

00:08:27.825 --> 00:08:29.865
All bills of exchange are checks.

00:08:30.105 --> 00:08:30.585
Nope.

00:08:30.855 --> 00:08:35.175
A check is a type of bill of exchange,
but not all bills are checks.

00:08:35.675 --> 00:08:40.745
A check has two special conditions
drawn on a bank and payable on demand.

00:08:41.255 --> 00:08:44.915
People also mix up a holder
and a holder in due course.

00:08:45.365 --> 00:08:47.705
A holder just holds the instrument.

00:08:48.095 --> 00:08:51.485
A holder in due course gets
special protection because

00:08:51.485 --> 00:08:52.955
they acquired it properly.

00:08:53.435 --> 00:08:57.515
A big misconception is that
promissory notes need acceptance.

00:08:57.665 --> 00:08:58.415
They don't.

00:08:58.805 --> 00:09:00.725
They are a promise from the maker.

00:09:01.235 --> 00:09:05.464
Bills of exchange need acceptance
by the drawee to become binding.

00:09:05.915 --> 00:09:10.865
Also, don't ignore grace days for
instruments payable after some time.

00:09:11.015 --> 00:09:13.175
Three grace days are usually added.

00:09:13.625 --> 00:09:18.995
Lastly, people forget that for the draw
or endorsers to be held liable, a proper

00:09:18.995 --> 00:09:21.814
notice of dishonor must usually be given.

