00:10:18.060 --> 00:10:20.099
Example, one question.

00:10:20.339 --> 00:10:23.910
Which of the following is a written
promise to pay a certain sum of

00:10:23.910 --> 00:10:28.709
money to a specified person or to
the bearer, a bill of exchange?

00:10:29.145 --> 00:10:30.224
B check.

00:10:30.494 --> 00:10:33.734
C promissory note D, demand draft.

00:10:34.185 --> 00:10:37.125
Understand the question
before moving to explanation.

00:10:37.665 --> 00:10:40.125
Step one is to analyze the question.

00:10:40.484 --> 00:10:43.185
The key phrase here is
written promise to pay.

00:10:43.545 --> 00:10:45.900
Step two is to recall our definitions.

00:10:46.685 --> 00:10:48.635
A bill of exchange is an order.

00:10:48.785 --> 00:10:51.185
A check is also an order on a bank.

00:10:51.575 --> 00:10:55.715
A promissory note is explicitly
defined as a written promise to pay.

00:10:56.105 --> 00:10:56.705
A demand.

00:10:56.705 --> 00:10:58.145
Draft is also an order.

00:10:58.505 --> 00:11:00.845
Step three is to match the definition.

00:11:01.235 --> 00:11:05.945
The phrase, written promise to pay is the
exact definition of a promissory note.

00:11:06.425 --> 00:11:08.945
Correct answer is C promissory note.

00:11:09.600 --> 00:11:11.520
Example two question.

00:11:11.790 --> 00:11:15.810
A check is always payable
A after a fixed period.

00:11:16.020 --> 00:11:23.400
B, on demand C at the option of the draw
D, only to a specific person understand

00:11:23.400 --> 00:11:25.320
the question before moving to explanation.

00:11:26.160 --> 00:11:28.830
First, let's understand
the nature of a check.

00:11:29.040 --> 00:11:30.840
It's used for immediate payment.

00:11:30.840 --> 00:11:36.390
Right now, let's evaluate the options
after a fixed period applies to time

00:11:36.390 --> 00:11:42.000
bills, not checks On demand means payment
is due as soon as the check is presented.

00:11:42.380 --> 00:11:46.250
This perfectly matches the legal
and practical definition of a check.

00:11:46.760 --> 00:11:49.040
At the option of the draw is incorrect.

00:11:49.460 --> 00:11:52.970
Only to a specific person is
also wrong because checks can

00:11:52.970 --> 00:11:54.230
be made payable to bearer.

00:11:54.830 --> 00:11:59.240
So by definition, a check is a bill
